# STL inspection tier (Tier 2b)

## What it does

`scripts/stl_inspect.py` loads STL files with trimesh and checks:
- Loadable, non-empty mesh
- Watertight (manifold) — warn, don't fail
- Volume in expected range per part
- Face count in expected range
- No collapsed axis (min extent > 0.1mm)
- No oversized axis (max extent within limit)
- Positive volume (normals not inverted)

## When to use

- **Primary geometry validation** — runs in <1s, pure Python, no browser/server
- After any geometry change, run `make stl-inspect` or the full pipeline
- The JSON report (`output/stl-inspection.json`) has per-part metrics the agent can read directly

## Expected ranges

Defined in `PART_EXPECTATIONS` dict in `stl_inspect.py`. Generous enough for
parameter sweeps. Update if adding new parts or significantly changing geometry.

## Relationship to other tiers

| Tier | Purpose | Needs |
|------|---------|-------|
| 2 | Render STLs + basic bbox | OpenSCAD |
| **2b** | **Deep geometry analysis** | **trimesh (pure Python)** |
| 3 | UI/viewer regression | Browser + server |

Tier 2b runs between 2 and 3. It validates geometry; Tier 3 validates the UI.
